air an Fhéinn :
nom . Fiann ;
gen . Féinne ;
dat . Féinn ;
originally “ a warrior band ” ; in tradition , both Scottish and Irish , applied specially to the band or bands of which Fionn Mac Cumhail was chief . On p . 17 , dat . an Fhéinn is now used as nom . ( See Duanaire Fhinn , Irish Text Society ; Fianaigecht , Royal Irish Academy ; Todd Lecture Series , XVI . ) .

